
[1]slate

   SLATE, n.

   1. An argillaceous stone which readily splits into plates; argillite;
   argillaceous shist.

   2. A piece of smooth argillaceous stone, used for covering buildings.

   3. A piece of smooth stone of the above species, used for writing on.

     SLATE, v.I. To cover with slate or plates of stone; as, to slate a
                    roof. [It does not signify to tile.]
